<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer12107934070927795084">James Patrick Donleavy was an Irish American author, born to Irish immigrants. He served in the U.S. Navy during World War II after which he moved to Ireland. In 1946 he began studies at Trinity College, Dublin, but left before taking a degree. He was first published in the Dublin literary periodical, Envoy.<br/><br/>See also <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J.P._Donleavy'>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J.P._Don...</a></span>
  <span id="freeText12107934070927795084" style="display:none">James Patrick Donleavy was an Irish American author, born to Irish immigrants. He served in the U.S. Navy during World War II after which he moved to Ireland. In 1946 he began studies at Trinity College, Dublin, but left before taking a degree. He was first published in the Dublin literary periodical, Envoy.<br /><br />See also <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J.P._Donleavy">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J.P._Don...</a></span>
